The paper discusses methods for comparing graphs and networks, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on systems biology suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a likely category, as well as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) which often deal with graph and network analysis. The use of citation networks and search terms suggests cs.DB (Databases) as a possible category, and the interdisciplinary nature of the paper could also make it relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
